OL,3,CWelsh Government 'palmed off' concerns
OL,4,Cat Ysgol Dyffryn Aman before attack
OL,6,FDuring the trial of the pupil
OL,7,Fresponsible for the stabbing, it
OL,8,Femerged that she had previously been
OL,9,Fcaught with a knife in Ysgol Dyffryn
OL,10,FAman in September 2023, resulting in a
OL,11,Ffixed-term exclusion.
OL,13,FWelsh Government guidelines state that
OL,14,Fthe use, or threatened use of an
OL,15,Foffensive weapon, can be considered an
OL,16,Fexceptional circumstance where a
OL,17,Fheadteacher can permanently exclude a
OL,18,Flearner for a first or one-off offence.
OL,20,FHowever, Ceri says this did not always
OL,21,Fhappen.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/15
