OL,3,CWelsh Government 'palmed off' concerns
OL,4,Cat Ysgol Dyffryn Aman before attack
OL,6,F"On more than one occasion, as a
OL,7,Fschool we had the conversation with
OL,8,Fthe local authority to explain someone
OL,9,Fwas carrying a knife and this is what
OL,10,Fwe would like to do... the response
OL,11,Ffrom the local authority was 'no we
OL,12,Fare not going to support you excluding
OL,13,Fthat person permanently'.
OL,15,F"Ultimately, what that means is, that
OL,16,Fpupils know that if they bring a knife
OL,17,Finto school, or another weapon into
OL,18,Fschool, there is no threat to their
OL,19,Fplace in school.
