OL,3,CWelsh Government 'palmed off' concerns
OL,4,Cat Ysgol Dyffryn Aman before attack
OL,6,F"I don't believe that I can work in a
OL,7,Fsystem where, to some extent, my hands
OL,8,Fhave been tied, and there is no
OL,9,Fsupport to do the things that are
OL,10,Fneeded to ensure that behaviour is as
OL,11,Fgood as it can be, and that staff and
OL,12,Fpupils are as safe as they can be
OL,13,Fwithin schools.
OL,15,F"The Government is asleep at the
OL,16,Fwheel, and I really believe that. I
OL,17,Fwant to see the guidelines give more
OL,18,Fpowers to schools so that it is more
OL,19,Fclear what schools can do and what
OL,20,Fschools cannot do - and that this
OL,21,Fenables schools to be more strict."
