OL,3,CWelsh Government 'palmed off' concerns
OL,4,Cat Ysgol Dyffryn Aman before attack
OL,6,FIn an interview with Y Byd ar Bedwar,
OL,7,FLynne Neagle MS, the Cabinet Secretary
OL,8,Ffor Education, said: "Any violence
OL,9,Ftowards teachers or staff is
OL,10,Fcompletely unacceptable. All schools
OL,11,Fshould be safe places for learners and
OL,12,Fstaff. All schools should have
OL,13,Fbehaviour policies in place which are
OL,14,Fconsistently implemented."
OL,16,F"As a government we have been focusing
OL,17,Freally strongly on tackling issues of
OL,18,Fpoor behaviour. We've got our
OL,19,Fbehaviour summit coming up where we're
OL,20,Fgoing to have an action focused look
OL,21,Fat what we need to do in this space.
OL,26,@pD@VOUvD@ZO]xD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/15
